About
Lord's Cricket Ground is known as the Home of Cricket and is owned by Marylebone Cricket Club - better known, throughout the cricketing world, as MCC. Founded in 1787, MCC is the world's most famous cricket club.

A Timeless Tribute to Cricket’s Glorious Legacy
Oct 2024 • Friends
Visiting Lord’s Cricket Ground and the MCC Museum is a dream come true for any cricket enthusiast. Steeped in history, Lord’s is often referred to as the “Home of Cricket,” and rightly so. From the moment you step onto its hallowed grounds, you feel the reverence for the sport that has captivated generations.

The guided tour is meticulously planned, offering an inside look at the Pavilion, Long Room, and the iconic Honours Boards. The highlight for me was standing at the edge of the field, imagining the greats who have played here.

The museum is equally impressive, housing the world-famous Ashes urn and other priceless cricket memorabilia. The exhibits are beautifully curated, providing a fascinating journey through cricket’s evolution.

Whether you’re a die-hard cricket fan or simply appreciate history, Lord’s offers a uniquely enriching experience that blends sport and heritage. An unforgettable visit!
Written October 28, 2024

Oct 2024 • Couples

From the artefacts in the museum, including the original Ashes urn and the first World Cup trophy, to the stories of players in the Long Room, this was a fascinating visit for lovers of cricket and those just curious alike. Our guide (Marcel?) was very professional, amusing and a mine of information. The tour also included a delicious meal in the Players’ Dining Room. I can thoroughly recommend this experience.
